The Greek Spot offers a wide array of good-tasting menu options, but the food quality doesn't justify the higher-than-average prices.  That's not to say that the Greek Spot is bad. In fact, I thought it was quite good! The vegetables tasted fresh, the seasoning on the fries was fantastic, and the meat was well-seasoned and tender. Food was ready quickly and the staff were responsive and knowledgeable about menu questions. There is adequate seating available- I won't say plentiful (I went at a time that was pretty slow), but outdoor seating and indoor seating for pairs or very small groups is available.  The portions were less than I expected from the cost. Having read other reviews I was expecting a full tray of fries and a bursting full pita, but got neither. The fries, which were fantastic, went quickly, and the only moderately-full pita left me wanting something more to eat (I'm usually a pretty light lunch-eater!). The less-than-generous portions combined with the slightly above-average cost for most of the menu options make it unlikely that this Greek Spot will become my go-to Greek spot.  If you're looking for something a bit more out of the way and are willing to spend a few dollars extra for lunch, the Greek Spot is likely to satisfy, but not dazzle you with an appealing location, common menu options, and maybe you will, maybe you won't seating.

The Moussaka was almost inedible, and resembled a door stop. It didn't have much flavor and tasted as if it came straight from a microwave. I will say the saving grace is that I ordered this food to go instead of sitting down at their restaurant so I didn't have to subject anybody else to this meal and commit them to an evening. I will not be returning and suggest avoiding this establishment.
